## React Input Handling ✅ IMPLEMENTED
- ✅ Use native property descriptor setters for React-controlled inputs
- ✅ Always dispatch input and change events after setting values
- ✅ Verify values were set correctly by reading them back
- ✅ Retry mechanism for values that don't stick immediately
- ✅ Separate handlers for input, textarea, select, checkbox/radio

## Page Stability Gates ✅ IMPLEMENTED
- ✅ Wait for DOM mutations to settle (500-800ms quiet period)
- ✅ Check for pending XHR/fetch requests via Performance API
- ✅ Apply before filling dropdown/autocomplete fields
- ✅ Prevents races with React remounting during autofill

## Implementation Details

### React Input Module (`shared/react-input.ts`)
Created dedicated module with these functions:
- `setReactInputValue()` - For text inputs and textareas
- `setReactInputValueWithRetry()` - With automatic retry logic
- `setReactCheckboxValue()` - For checkboxes and radio buttons
- `setReactSelectValue()` - For select dropdowns

### Stability Functions (`content.ts`)
- `waitForPageStability()` - Monitors DOM mutations
- `hasPendingRequests()` - Checks Performance API
- `waitForStability()` - Combined stability check

### Applied Throughout
All value-setting operations now use React-compatible setters:
- Main autofill (`executeFillPlan`)
- Per-field smart autofill (`fillFieldWithValue`)
- Browser-use actions (`executeBrowserUseActions`)
- Shadow DOM fields
- Regular and custom dropdown/autocomplete fields

