## Custom Dropdown Click Targets ✅ IMPLEMENTED
- ✅ Never assume the matched option element is the click target
- ✅ Always search for clickable children (`button`, `[role="button"]`, `div[class*="item"]`) inside option elements
- ✅ Many dropdown libraries (Eightfold, etc.) wrap `<button>` inside `<li role="presentation">`
- ✅ The LI is just a wrapper — clicking it does nothing; the button has the React onClick handler
- ✅ After clicking, verify `element.value` actually changed
- ✅ If click didn't work, fall back to React native setter as last resort

## Cross-Origin Iframe Handling ✅ IMPLEMENTED
- ✅ Use `"all_frames": true` in manifest.json to inject into iframes
- ✅ Implement `postMessage` bridge for parent-to-iframe communication
- ✅ Parent frame forwards autofill/suggestion triggers to all iframes
- ✅ Each iframe runs its own field detection independently
- ✅ Common ATS platforms using iframes: Greenhouse, Lever

## Multi-Page Form Navigation ✅ IMPLEMENTED
- ✅ After autofill, auto-click "Save and Continue" / "Next" / "Continue" buttons
- ✅ Click navigation even if no fields were filled (optional/pre-filled pages)
- ✅ Re-scan fields after page transition
- ✅ Workday uses multi-step wizards that require explicit advancement

