## Quick Reference Checklist

Before submitting any code:
- [ ] Used React-compatible input setters (no direct `input.value = x`)
- [ ] Applied page stability gates before DOM manipulation
- [ ] Handled both regular and shadow DOM scenarios
- [ ] Dispatched proper events after value changes
- [ ] Tested on React-based websites
- [ ] For dropdowns: click child elements (button), not wrapper elements (li/div)
- [ ] For dropdowns: verify input value changed after click, fallback if not
- [ ] Considered iframe-embedded forms (all_frames + postMessage)
- [ ] For multi-page forms: auto-advance after fill
- [ ] Checked known-issues.md for similar past problems
- [ ] Documented any new issues encountered
- [ ] Referenced relevant ADRs in code comments if applicable
